rComments: I had Dr. Girard in my first semester. He was an excellent and caring man. However the course content did seem dry at times. Opt for the 1.5 hour lectures twice a week over the 3 hour lecture once a week - you will get more out of the class.

Prof Girard was easily my favourite prof last semester. He is clearly SUPER passionate about what he teaches and his students. I wasn't sure if I'd like this class but it amazed me. It was a lot of fun and eye-opening. Do the readings though! Super memorable class + prof, highly recommend taking this class even if it's not mandatory for you.

He's a pretty caring prof but he basically just reads off the slides so you really don't have to go to class. Just read the slides and the textbook and you'll be good. Exams (2 midterms and 1 final) have super specific questions though.

Good choice of prof, very chill guy. Makes really great connections between course material and real world issues, which enriches learning. Interesting guest speakers too. Midterms and finals are a breeze.

Horribly disorganized takes months to mark everything. Very unclear with exam and assignment criteria and expectations. Re-weighs grading randomly. Cancelled our final exam on the last day of class - one week before the final. Does not answer emails or takes a ridiculous amount of time. Hard to reach and cancels scheduled meetings.

Prof GG is super nice and tries his best to make classes interesting, however they aren't always pertinent to what will be tested on the exam - those are pretty much from the textbook. There's a website with exams questions though! Tough marking on the group project.

Took Sociopolitical and Economic Perspectives in Health with Prof. Girard. Reading all the readings is essential for all exams, but he is extremely fair and he questions are super straight forward, no tricks. Gives questions on videos we watch in classat home which are super easy, make sure you have friends for the group project. Excellent prof!

First midterm is the hardest so ATTENDANCE IS MANDATORY for first half of the course. The rest is based on the textbook and slides (heavy readings per midterms and exams). Make sure you choose a good group for the group project because its worth just as much as the exam. Great prof, he is very nice and helpful. Take HSS courses with him for sure.

Great Prof. Probably one of the best professors at U of O. He is very funny and he makes it worth going to class. You must buy the textbook and read it completely. Especially for the last part of the course. A lot of work in this class, but it gives you a lot of chances to do good.

Fantastic professor! He is very interesting and super friendly. You have to do a good amount of reading and there is a group project worth 30%. All the important information is on the slide and in the textbook, but I enjoyed going to his class! My favorite professor so far!

Really nice guy. Always happy and cheery, and very funny. The lectures are completely useless, though. The exams are entirely from the textbook - but sometimes there are questions on videos/guest speakers (he'll tell you). The exams were HARD. It was a stressful course, since it had 2 midterms, a 15 page essay, a 3-5 minute video, and a final.
AWESOME PROF !!! Seriously always had the most entertaining classes . I didn't find his midterms easy but overall great prof and class. He's also hilarious.

Girard is a genuinely kind person and any comments attacking his character should be disregarded. That being said, everything else is true. Attending the lectures was completely useless (most of which consisted of watching movies that were not exam material or watching oral presentations from your classmates).

J'ai vraiment adoré comme professeur! Plutôt que de juste lire ce qui est sur les diaporama/dans les livres (ce qu'on peut faire par soi-même), il donne plus des exemples concrets. Il prend le temps de parler avec les étudiants avant et après les cours si on a des questions. Il est assez direct pour les examens, le livre, mais assez simple.

If you can avoid it, do NOT take a class with this prof.  Although his class is easy, he has no care in the world whatsoever for the class or students in it.  Very arrogant prof, takes forever to post grades online or to tell you what will be on the exam.

Ce professeur n'enseigne pas. Je n'ai pas appris grand chose dans ce cours qui aurait pu être utile mais bon. Si vous l'avez faites juste lire le manuel et pour le travail choisir le sujet le plus simple possible. C'était un cours de niveau du secondaire

C'est une personne très gentille, très ouverte aux commentaires. Cependant il n'enseigne pas du tout, il ne fait que parler de choses inutiles et il est plus ou moins claire dans ses directives. Pour les examens, il faut simplement lire le manuel. Je ne considère pas cet homme comme un prof. Il n'enseigne pas. Il jase.

He does not teach the material in class and expects you to memorize the entire textbook (even the smallest details). His M.C. exams are vague and hard to understand and are much harder than he makes it out to be... he also takes forever to reply to e-mails and he also changed the entire exam outline a week before the final with no notice

Straightforward material-wise until you hit the exam for this course - at least if HE writes it. Questions were vaguely worded and I left the exam feeling confident until I got my mark back. Plays word games in questions but isn't very good with them, defying common sense at points. HIS course is common sense made unecessarily difficult!
interesting prof, the class required no textbook. midterm were rather easy if you attended class. overall very interesting class, highly recommended over the other HSS1101 profs.

He is the best. The class was so much fun, and he puts forth the effort to make sure the material is enjoyable to the students. He puts the students first, and that is why he is a excellent prof. Love him!!

The best proff i ever had thus far! he's always there when you have questions, his class is mandatory to attend (10%) but he always has entertaining ways to give out his lectures. his TA'a were amazing too. and all most every one got A+, there was a midterm (10 questions) and no final exam STELLAR. i would definitely recommend his class.
Best prof ever! I wish all classes were this fun!

I agree that he is lively and fun to listen to, but he is EXTREMELY disorganized and doesn't seem to know what he is teaching. He updated the syllabus 5 times, and changed the exam content 2 days before the exam. Doesn't answer emails and puts forward a good face when it is quite obvious that he wants to do as little work as possible. Lazy.

He's a very lively teacher and very down to earth. His jokes are really funny and he tries to make the class fun. He basically tells you everything you need to know for the exams and as long as you read the slides once, you should not get any lower than an A-. Very easy class!
He's AMAZING! and the T.A's were adorable! This class was the easiest class I had this semester and the funnest as well. He's very enthusiastic and makes everything Fun!

Professor Girard is great! His classes are interesting, and funny! We had presentations, team work, and essay. It was fun to do all this work. Prof is always ready to help you any time! Every part of this class was amazing! The Prof is very friendly! Great teacher!!!

Excellent professor, very enthusiastic and energetic, applies topics to real life. Very helpful and flexible. Keeps the course interesting. Course outline is exact and everything is provided on virtual campus including your grade.

This prof takes the time to talk to everyone individually which is great... and give feedback to improve; the feedback is always very helpful. Girard is very involved with the students, and he likes to walk around and talk to everyone before and after class. --He's a very fair marker, and this class is an easy A. (Super fair midterm & assignments)

A great teacher, very interesting to listen to and very interested in what he's teaching.  He like to go talk randomly to student before class and give them Hi 5!  I had never seen that great attitude before.  Very approchable and cool and if you attend class, you should get A+.

Awesome prof! His classes were always interesting, the material was well organized and very clear. The project was a lot of fun! Very helpful, very original, very cool! :) A little suggestion for people taking this class: make your project and your report as original as possible! I got 104%, thanks to a bonus for originality!

Incredible Prof! Plus he's good looking too! I looking forward to his classes every wednesday and friday morning. Out of 120 students he has noticed me, and he always chitchats with all of the students. The presentation comments and improvement advice is spectacular. I would recomend him to anyone who takes this class. Prepare to laugh.
He was incredible teacher!  Absolutely awesome.  The only class I ever looked forward to going to.  If you have the opportunity to have him a teacher, do it!
